					currentTab = btn.getAttribute('data-tab');

					Object.keys(sliders).forEach(key => {
						sliders[key].style.display = key === currentTab ? 'block' : 'none';
					});

					updateInfoPanel(currentTab);
				});
			});

			// ----------------------------------------------------
			// RENDERING MODULES
			// ----------------------------------------------------

			// 1. GRAVITY WAVES
			function drawGravityWaves(cx, cy) {
				const gSpeed = parseFloat(pgSpeed.value);
				const gAmp = parseFloat(pgAmp.value);
				const gC = parseFloat(pgC.value);
				const gMouse = parseFloat(pgMouse.value);
				const bhR = 38;

				const currentRadius = bhR * (0.85 + 0.15 * Math.sin(t * 0.003));
				const bh1X = cx + currentRadius * Math.cos(gSpeed * t);
				const bh1Y = cy + currentRadius * Math.sin(gSpeed * t);
				const bh2X = cx - currentRadius * Math.cos(gSpeed * t);
				const bh2Y = cy - currentRadius * Math.sin(gSpeed * t);

				gridPoints.forEach(p => {
					const dx = p.origX - cx;
					const dy = p.origY - cy;
					const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
					const d = Math.max(dist, 10);
					const theta = Math.atan2(dy, dx);

					const phase = 2 * theta - 2 * gSpeed * (t - d / gC);
					const amp = (gAmp * 150) / (d + 120);

					const offsetStrength = amp * Math.cos(phase);
					let offsetX = offsetStrength * Math.cos(theta) * 0.45;
					let offsetY = offsetStrength * Math.sin(theta) * 0.45;

					if (mouseActive && gMouse > 0) {
						const mdx = mouseX - p.origX;
						const mdy = mouseY - p.origY;
						const mdist = Math.sqrt(mdx * mdx + mdy * mdy);
						if (mdist < 240) {
							const pull = (240 - mdist) / 240 * gMouse;
							offsetX += (mdx / (mdist + 1)) * pull;
							offsetY += (mdy / (mdist + 1)) * pull;
						}
					}

					const renderX = p.origX + offsetX;
					const renderY = p.origY + offsetY;
					const alpha = Math.max(0.08, 0.72 - (d / (width * 0.65)));

					ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(192, 196, 204, ${alpha})`;
					ctx.beginPath();
					const r = d < 120 ? 1.8 : 1.1;
					ctx.arc(renderX, renderY, r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
					ctx.fill();
				});

				// Draw Binary BHs
				ctx.shadowBlur = 10;
				ctx.shadowColor = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)';
				ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 1)';
				ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5)';
				ctx.lineWidth = 1;

				ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(bh1X, bh1Y, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
				ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(bh2X, bh2Y, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
				ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
			}

			// 2. SINGING BOWL SOUND WAVE PROPAGATION (縱波/壓縮波粒子可視化)
			function drawSingingBowl(cx, cy) {
				const bDir = pbDir.value;
				const bSize = pbSize.value;
				const bAction = pbAction.value;
				const bFreq = parseFloat(pbFreq.value);
				const bAmp = parseFloat(pbAmp.value);

				const bowlRadius = Math.min(width, height) * (bSize === 'large' ? 0.38 : 0.28);
				const particleRadius = bSize === 'large' ? 1.8 : 0.95;

				// Rubbing rim trigger calculations
				const mdx = mouseX - cx;
				const mdy = mouseY - cy;
				const mdist = Math.sqrt(mdx * mdx + mdy * mdy);
				const isNearRim = mouseActive && Math.abs(mdist - bowlRadius) < 55;
				const energyFactor = isNearRim ? 1.0 : 0.05;

				// Rubbing action: emit sound particles continuously from the rub angle location
				if (bAction === 'rub' && isNearRim) {
					const rubAngle = Math.atan2(mdy, mdx);
					
					// Emit sound waves pointing outward or inward
					// We spawn particles near the rub angle with small distribution
					const spawnCount = bSize === 'large' ? 4 : 8;
					for (let i = 0; i < spawnCount; i++) {
						const angle = rubAngle + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4;
						const dir = bDir; // 'both', 'out', 'in'
						soundWaveParticles.push({
							angle: angle,
							distTraveled: 0,
							speed: 1.5 + Math.random() * 1.5,
							amplitude: bAmp * 1.1,
							opacity: 0.9,
							direction: dir === 'both' ? (Math.random() > 0.5 ? 'out' : 'in') : dir
						});
					}
				}

				// Render vibrating bowl rim
				// Quadrupole flex vibration shape for the bowl rim: expands/contracts
				const flexMode = 4; // Fundamental mode for singing bowl deformation
				const flexAmp = isNearRim ? 6 : 1.5;
				
				ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)';
				ctx.lineWidth = 2.5;
				ctx.beginPath();
				
				for (let a = 0; a <= 360; a += 2) {
					const angle = (a * Math.PI) / 180;
					// Bowl rim flex deformation radius offset
					const flexOffset = flexAmp * Math.sin(flexMode * angle) * Math.sin(t * bFreq * Math.PI * 2);
					const r = bowlRadius + flexOffset;
					const px = cx + r * Math.cos(angle);
					const py = cy + r * Math.sin(angle);
					if (a === 0) ctx.moveTo(px, py);
					else ctx.lineTo(px, py);
				}
				ctx.closePath();
				ctx.stroke();

				// Update and Draw Soundwave particles (Longitudinal wave representation)
				for (let i = soundWaveParticles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
					const p = soundWaveParticles[i];
					
					// Move propagation distance
					if (p.direction === 'out') {
						p.distTraveled += p.speed;
					} else {
						p.distTraveled += p.speed; // Moving inward
					}

					// Decay opacity over age
					p.opacity -= 0.008;

					// Check boundaries
					const currentDist = p.direction === 'out' ? bowlRadius + p.distTraveled : bowlRadius - p.distTraveled;
					
					// Remove faded or out-of-screen particles
					if (p.opacity <= 0 || currentDist < 0 || currentDist > Math.max(width, height) * 0.75) {
						soundWaveParticles.splice(i, 1);
						continue;
					}

					// Longitudinal wave compression oscillation offset
					// Sound is a compression wave; particles vibrate forward and backward along wave path direction
					const waveNumber = bSize === 'large' ? 0.08 : 0.16; // Frequency of compression bands
					const waveOffset = p.amplitude * Math.sin(p.distTraveled * waveNumber - t * bFreq * 10);

					// Render coordinates
					const actualRadius = currentDist + waveOffset;
					const renderX = cx + actualRadius * Math.cos(p.angle);
					const renderY = cy + actualRadius * Math.sin(p.angle);

					// Color shift based on compression state: compressed areas are brighter/whiter
					const isCompressed = Math.sin(p.distTraveled * waveNumber - t * bFreq * 10) > 0.7;
					const colorVal = isCompressed ? 255 : 200;
					
					ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${colorVal}, ${colorVal + 5}, ${colorVal + 15}, ${p.opacity})`;
					ctx.beginPath();
					ctx.arc(renderX, renderY, particleRadius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
					ctx.fill();
				}

				// Draw rubbing feedback circle
				if (isNearRim && bAction === 'rub') {
					ctx.beginPath();
					ctx.arc(mouseX, mouseY, 15, 0, Math.PI * 2);
					ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12)';
					ctx.fill();
					ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25)';
					ctx.stroke();
				}
			}

			// 3. FRAME DRUM RESONANCE
			function drawFrameDrum(cx, cy) {
				const dTen = parseFloat(pdTension.value);
				const dDecay = parseFloat(pdDecay.value);
				const dMode = parseInt(pdMode.value);
				const drumRadius = Math.min(width, height) * 0.35;

				// Draw Drum Shell
				ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12)';
				ctx.lineWidth = 3;
				ctx.beginPath();
				ctx.arc(cx, cy, drumRadius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
				ctx.stroke();

				// Solver updates
				drumNodes.forEach(node => {
					let force = -dTen * node.z;

					// Harmonic Mode excitation force
					if (dMode > 0) {
						const dist = Math.sqrt(node.x * node.x + node.y * node.y);
						const theta = Math.atan2(node.y, node.x);
						let besselApprox = 0;
						if (dMode === 1) { // Mode (0,1) Fundamental
							besselApprox = Math.cos((dist / drumRadius) * Math.PI * 0.5);
						} else if (dMode === 2) { // Mode (1,1) Split dipole
							besselApprox = Math.sin((dist / drumRadius) * Math.PI) * Math.cos(theta);
						} else if (dMode === 3) { // Mode (0,2) Concentric ring
							besselApprox = Math.cos((dist / drumRadius) * Math.PI * 1.5);
						}
						
						force += besselApprox * Math.sin(t * 0.08) * 0.15;
					}

					node.velocity += force;
					node.velocity *= (1 - dDecay);
					node.z += node.velocity;
				});

				// Oblique 3D mesh projection
				const skewY = 0.55; 

				drumNodes.forEach(node => {
					const projX = cx + node.x;
					const projY = cy + node.y * skewY - node.z * 1.1;

					let lightness = 80;
					if (node.z > 1) {
						lightness = Math.min(100, 80 + node.z * 1.2);
					} else if (node.z < -1) {
						lightness = Math.max(30, 80 + node.z * 0.8);
					}

					const alpha = Math.max(0.15, Math.min(0.85, 0.5 + node.z * 0.04));

					ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${lightness + 40}, ${lightness + 45}, ${lightness + 55}, ${alpha})`;
					ctx.beginPath();
					const size = Math.max(1, 1.4 + Math.abs(node.z) * 0.08);
					ctx.arc(projX, projY, size, 0, Math.PI * 2);
					ctx.fill();
				});
			}

			// 4. DMT VISUAL FLOW (FULL-SCREEN FLUID FIELD)
			function drawDmtFlow(cx, cy) {
				const dmSym = parseInt(pdmSym.value);
				const dmSpeed = parseFloat(pdmSpeed.value);
				const dmComp = parseFloat(pdmComp.value);
				const dmGlow = parseFloat(pdmGlow.value);

				// Max screen boundaries
				const maxRadius = Math.max(width, height) * 0.85;

				dmtParticles.forEach(p => {
					// Dynamic vector flow field coordinates
					const angle = dmComp * (p.r * 0.004) + Math.sin(p.theta * dmSym) + t * 0.005;
					
					// Move along flow field vectors
					p.theta += dmSpeed * Math.cos(angle) * p.speed;
					p.r += Math.sin(angle) * p.speed * 1.5;

					// Reset if particle moves out of boundaries
					if (p.r > maxRadius || p.r < 5) {
						p.r = 15 + Math.random() * 80;
						p.theta = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
					}

					// Mouse gravity attraction local warp
					let mOffsetX = 0;
					let mOffsetY = 0;
					if (mouseActive) {
						const px = p.r * Math.cos(p.theta);
						const py = p.r * Math.sin(p.theta);
						const pdx = mouseX - (cx + px);
						const pdy = mouseY - (cy + py);
						const pDist = Math.sqrt(pdx * pdx + pdy * pdy);
						if (pDist < 250) {
							const warpPower = (250 - pDist) / 250 * 3.5;
							mOffsetX = (pdx / (pDist + 1)) * warpPower;
							mOffsetY = (pdy / (pDist + 1)) * warpPower;
						}
					}

					// Render N-fold kaleidoscope symmetry reflections (Full Screen)
					for (let i = 0; i < dmSym; i++) {
						const symTheta = p.theta + (i * Math.PI * 2) / dmSym;
						
						const px = cx + p.r * Math.cos(symTheta) + mOffsetX;
						const py = cy + p.r * Math.sin(symTheta) + mOffsetY;

						let colorStr = 'rgba(213, 215, 219,'; // Bright plaster
						if (p.colorIndex === 1) colorStr = 'rgba(150, 154, 166,'; // Concrete gray
						else if (p.colorIndex === 2) colorStr = 'rgba(255, 255, 255,'; // White

						ctx.shadowBlur = dmGlow * 18;
						ctx.shadowColor = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4)';

						ctx.fillStyle = `${colorStr} ${p.alpha})`;
						ctx.beginPath();
						ctx.arc(px, py, 1.6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
						ctx.fill();
					}
				});
				ctx.shadowBlur = 0; // Reset
			}

			// Main loop selector
			function animate() {
				t += 1;
				ctx.fillStyle = '#000000';
				ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

				const cx = width / 2;
				const cy = height / 2;

				if (currentTab === 'gravity') {
					drawGravityWaves(cx, cy);
				} else if (currentTab === 'bowl') {
					drawSingingBowl(cx, cy);
				} else if (currentTab === 'drum') {
					drawFrameDrum(cx, cy);
				} else if (currentTab === 'dmt') {
					drawDmtFlow(cx, cy);
				}

				requestAnimationFrame(animate);
			}

			animate();
		</script>
	</body>
</html>
